.TH LOA-OBSIDIAN-OPEN 1 "2026-03-23" "Library Of Alexandria" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
obsidian open \- Open Obsidian vault or jump to one managed note
.SH SYNOPSIS
alexandria> obsidian open
.br
alexandria> obsidian open b0001
.br
alexandria> obsidian open /path/to/your/vault
.SH DESCRIPTION
Launches Obsidian using the configured vault path.
.br
If an item reference is provided (ID/ISBN/title/author/composer),
Alexandria resolves the item and opens its note via \fBobsidian://\fR URI.
.br
If a filesystem path is provided, that path is treated as the vault path.
.br
The Alexandria CLI stays running after opening.
.br
If no vault path is configured, set one with:
.br
\fBexport obsidian <vault_path>\fR
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
alexandria> obsidian open
.TP
alexandria> obsidian open b0001
.TP
alexandria> obsidian open "Das Kapital"
.TP
alexandria> obsidian open ~/Documents/MyVault
.SH SEE ALSO
loa(1), loa-export-obsidian(1), loa-obsidian-sync(1), loa-obsidian-doctor(1)
.SH AUTHOR
